        "username": "NoahR",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/noahr/{size}/2194_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-02-18T00:45:10.824Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened for my birthday, along with a delicious 1977 Boak. A bit austere and tannic, keeping with the vintage, despite ample time in decanter. Decent density but not sweet. Tobacco and leafy in spades, a touch of saddle leather, cassis and tart berry fruit.</p>\n<p>This is a solid and rich Bordeaux, but it lacked finesse and never really blossomed into anything interesting, even after long decant. It has the density and tannins to age further. Whether it picks up a tertiary nuance that delights is a separate matter. I have one more bottle that I\u2019ll keep for another decade.</p>\n<p>I expect First Growths to blow me out of the water. This did not.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 7,
        "updated_at": "2023-02-18T00:45:10.824Z",
