      {
        "id": 4012024,
        "name": null,
        "username": "NoahR",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/noahr/{size}/2194_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-02-18T18:09:44.133Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Andrew - I appreciate the sentiment, but I do love Bordeaux, love the general style of HB, and have drunk a few hundred bottles of left bank Bordeaux, so it\u2019s not a matter of style, it\u2019s a matter of firm expectations not being met.</p>\n<p>Jeff - you are right on all accounts - this was not a bretty bottle, but it was an auction bottle, so I cannot be assured of provenance. I expected more, given the year and the wine, and this was perhaps an off bottle. It wasn\u2019t tannic, it was tannic for 96. It wasn\u2019t austere, it was austere for my expectations of 96 HB. Your impression that it is a good-but-not-great HB is confirmed. I was just hoping for more\u2026</p>\n<p>I am in agreement that many other Bordeaux often match or surpass the first growths, which I why I rarely spring for them. My favorite Bordeaux in recent memory have been 86 Rauzan-Segla, 86 PLL, 89 Pichon Baron and 82 Gruaud Larose, all of which trade at 1/3 the price of any first growth from the same year. All of which were much more enjoyable than this bottle.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> N</p>",
