        "created_at": "2023-02-18T19:31:49.669Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I am a big Haut-Brion fan and have it back to 1924 in my personal cellar, but if you think \u201cgood bottles are never bretty\u201d you must have a very high threshold for volatile phenols <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/sweat_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":sweat_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":sweat_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>It has however been a lot cleaner in the new millennium, with the exception of 2007.</p>",
